22
00:02:37,750 --> 00:02:43,660
♫  yet you wore short-sleeved clothing  ♫

23
00:02:43,660 --> 00:02:45,520
Cry.

24
00:02:46,640 --> 00:02:50,050
At least cry, you idiot.

25
00:02:54,660 --> 00:02:57,680
Cry louder!

26
00:03:02,260 --> 00:03:05,350
♫   Spring has come,  ♫

27
00:03:06,730 --> 00:03:11,770
♫  and you're standing in front of me again  ♫

28
00:03:11,770 --> 00:03:14,280
♫  Staring at me...  ♫

29
00:03:14,280 --> 00:03:17,250
I'll stay by your side.

30
00:03:18,450 --> 00:03:20,920
I won't go anywhere.

31
00:03:23,210 --> 00:03:25,880
Cry whenever you want to cry.

32
00:03:27,930 --> 00:03:31,430
♫  Your glance alone  ♫

33
00:03:31,430 --> 00:03:35,580
♫  is too much for me,  ♫

34
00:03:35,580 --> 00:03:44,210
♫  so I watch over you, like this  ♫

35
00:03:51,460 --> 00:03:56,110
♫  After seasons passed,  ♫

36
00:03:58,400 --> 00:04:02,560
♫  the sunlight is warm today  ♫

37
00:04:06,680 --> 00:04:10,140
♫  Spring has come,  ♫

38
00:04:11,160 --> 00:04:17,740
♫  and you're in front of me again,  ♫

39
00:04:19,800 --> 00:04:27,380
♫  staring at me, then smiling at me  ♫

40
00:04:28,560 --> 00:04:30,370
Don't go.

41
00:04:30,400 --> 00:04:34,900
Please don't go.

42
00:04:35,900 --> 00:04:39,410
Don't go.

43
00:04:39,410 --> 00:04:43,620
♫  is too much for me,  ♫

44
00:04:43,620 --> 00:04:47,920
♫  so it (my breathing) stops like this  ♫

45
00:04:47,920 --> 00:04:50,190
Is it okay...

46
00:04:50,190 --> 00:04:52,470
for me to stay next to you?

47
00:04:52,470 --> 00:04:57,560
♫  She turns around,  ♫

48
00:04:57,560 --> 00:05:04,510
♫  and I feel like I can't breathe  ♫

49
00:05:04,510 --> 00:05:08,150
♫  Your movements alone  ♫

50
00:05:08,150 --> 00:05:09,900
♫  are too much  ♫

51
00:05:09,900 --> 00:05:13,400
Will I not be able to see you now, Senior?

52
00:05:13,400 --> 00:05:17,710
If I knew it'd be like this, I would've said a better farewell earlier.

53
00:05:18,910 --> 00:05:23,780
In the end, you and Grandmother left.

54
00:05:30,320 --> 00:05:32,220
Goodbye.

55
00:05:32,220 --> 00:05:34,810
Everyone take care.

56
00:05:46,960 --> 00:05:51,610

57
00:06:06,370 --> 00:06:08,690

58
00:06:08,690 --> 00:06:12,210
Gosh, this guy... really.

59
00:06:13,020 --> 00:06:14,620
Temporary leave of absence?

60
00:06:14,620 --> 00:06:15,760
Yes.

61
00:06:15,760 --> 00:06:19,570
He's been saying that he wants to take a break due to health problems,

62
00:06:19,570 --> 00:06:24,270
but he became worse all of a sudden and had no choice.

63
00:06:24,270 --> 00:06:27,760
He's sorry that he couldn't see you before leaving.

64
00:06:27,760 --> 00:06:31,430
Regardless, there are things called procedures.

65
00:06:31,430 --> 00:06:35,070
You need to immediately find a temporary music teacher.

66
00:06:35,070 --> 00:06:36,930
Yes.

67
00:06:36,930 --> 00:06:39,630
You take over the homeroom position.

68
00:06:39,630 --> 00:06:41,710
Yes.  What?

69
00:06:41,710 --> 00:06:47,660
Ah, Second Year, Room 3's class... I should... Uh, yes.

70
00:06:56,220 --> 00:06:57,880
Hey.

71
00:06:57,880 --> 00:06:59,660
Where's Sungyeol?

72
00:07:00,500 --> 00:07:02,810
Why isn't he coming?

73
00:07:04,050 --> 00:07:06,930
You ask him yourself.

74
00:07:08,310 --> 00:07:10,450
Your answers are short!

75
00:07:10,450 --> 00:07:12,030
Did you eat something wrong?!

76
00:07:12,030 --> 00:07:15,140
Even my heart aches this much.

77
00:07:15,140 --> 00:07:18,270
It must be even more painful for my Woohyun.

78
00:07:19,770 --> 00:07:21,390
Aren't you worried?

79
00:07:21,390 --> 00:07:23,630
You need to worry about yourself.

80
00:07:23,630 --> 00:07:26,710
Because I hate you the most right now!

81
00:07:26,710 --> 00:07:29,740
Can't you see why everyone's like this?

82
00:07:29,740 --> 00:07:34,080
Did everyone here take some drugs?!

83
00:07:38,360 --> 00:07:39,590
Okay, I caught you!

84
00:07:39,590 --> 00:07:41,690
Teacher, Teacher that's a new one. Change it with this one!

85
00:07:41,690 --> 00:07:44,950
This one, too. Everyone, stop what you're doing!

86
00:07:48,060 --> 00:07:50,450
It's not P.E. class.

87
00:07:50,450 --> 00:07:53,430
Starting from today, I am your temporary homeroom teacher.

88
00:07:53,430 --> 00:07:56,140
 Oh my god!  No way!

89
00:07:56,140 --> 00:07:57,610
 No way!

90
00:07:57,610 --> 00:07:59,900
Oh, such an enthusiastic response!

91
00:07:59,900 --> 00:08:03,060
What about our homeroom teacher?

92
00:08:03,060 --> 00:08:06,090
That's what I want to ask.

93
00:08:06,090 --> 00:08:08,780
Hey, how much of a hard time did you give your teacher

94
00:08:08,780 --> 00:08:11,130
that he--

95
00:08:11,130 --> 00:08:14,970
Why are there empty seats?  That's Shin Woohyun and who else?

96
00:08:14,970 --> 00:08:17,030
Lee Seulbi and Hwang Sungyeol.

97
00:08:17,030 --> 00:08:21,620
Lee Seulbi sent an absence notice, but there's no word from Hwang Sungyeol yet.

98
00:08:21,620 --> 00:08:24,750
All the close ones are absent together?

99
00:08:24,750 --> 00:08:28,250
From now on, unexcused absences and tardiness are prohibited.

100
00:08:28,250 --> 00:08:29,680
Disobedience is prohibited.

101
00:08:29,680 --> 00:08:31,150
Sleeping is prohibited.

102
00:08:31,150 --> 00:08:33,010
Chit-chatting is prohibiting.

103
00:08:33,010 --> 00:08:36,350
And dating within the classroom is PROHIBITED!

104
00:08:37,270 --> 00:08:39,710
Complaining is prohibited.

105
00:09:16,430 --> 00:09:18,750
Not a resignation but a temporary leave of absence!

106
00:09:18,750 --> 00:09:22,080
It's not like he's sick or anything. Does it make sense that he's taking a temporary leave of absence?

107
00:09:22,080 --> 00:09:24,070
What kind of a teacher is this irresponsible?

108
00:09:24,070 --> 00:09:30,120
Usually, people with lots of responsibility overreact in situations like this.

109
00:09:33,400 --> 00:09:35,100
Can you give me some pain relievers?

110
00:09:35,100 --> 00:09:36,000
Sure.

111
00:09:38,160 --> 00:09:41,510
Teacher, is something giving you a headache?

112
00:09:41,510 --> 00:09:44,780
You're asking for pain relievers often these days.

113
00:09:48,560 --> 00:09:51,630
Teacher Kwangsik won't get fired, right? Right?

114
00:09:51,630 --> 00:09:53,950
You're subtly worried about him.

115
00:09:53,950 --> 00:09:57,230
No.

116
00:09:57,230 --> 00:09:59,720
He has no skills, he's not brave, he's not good looking.

117
00:09:59,720 --> 00:10:01,700
It'll be a big deal if he gets fired.

118
00:10:01,700 --> 00:10:04,550
He's old, too. What would happen if he doesn't have a job either?

119
00:10:04,550 --> 00:10:05,910
Who's going to take him?

120
00:10:05,910 --> 00:10:09,050
You should have been nicer when he was here!

121
00:10:09,050 --> 00:10:13,160
Either way, Shin Woohyun and Seulbi are mourning,

122
00:10:13,160 --> 00:10:17,210
but why is Hwang Sungyeol absent without notice?

123
00:10:17,210 --> 00:10:19,910
Sungyeol didn't come to school?

124
00:10:21,580 --> 00:10:24,080
Sungyeol's been causing trouble these days.

125
00:10:24,080 --> 00:10:25,800
He was the perfect son.

126
00:10:25,800 --> 00:10:30,570
I should've done something as soon as he became friends with Shin Woohyun.

127
00:10:32,160 --> 00:10:36,830
Just because he's friends with somebody, doesn't mean he'll become a problem child.

128
00:10:36,830 --> 00:10:39,250
Woohyun isn't a bad kid, either.

129
00:10:44,250 --> 00:10:48,760
It's weird how Teacher Ahn gets sensitive whenever there's something about Sungyeol.

130
00:10:48,760 --> 00:10:50,910
Does she have some sort of relationship with Sungyeol?

131
00:10:50,910 --> 00:10:54,900
Sungyeol and Woohyun are handsome.

132
00:10:54,900 --> 00:10:58,750
When those two are together, they're like idols.

133
00:10:58,750 --> 00:11:03,040
Achoo! I don't want to hear it! Achoo!

134
00:11:03,040 --> 00:11:07,910
  The person you have dialed is unavailable.

135
00:11:25,110 --> 00:11:27,310

136
00:11:40,820 --> 00:11:43,610
 Mom's getting married.

137
00:11:58,180 --> 00:12:02,690
He should order someone else to be his "Bread Shuttle."  Why is he telling us to do this? 
  (A bullied person who is ordered to retrieve snacks)

138
00:12:02,690 --> 00:12:04,060
Do you think he caught on?

139
00:12:04,060 --> 00:12:06,300
That's not possible.

140
00:12:07,110 --> 00:12:10,070
I do feel bad for Shin Woohyun.

141
00:12:10,070 --> 00:12:13,520
When my grandma passed away, I cried a lot.

142
00:12:13,520 --> 00:12:15,900
He didn't cry.

143
00:12:15,900 --> 00:12:18,720
You should have cried for him then.

144
00:12:21,060 --> 00:12:23,210
Ah, we went to keep an eye on Chunsik,

145
00:12:23,210 --> 00:12:24,650
in case he decided to confess.

146
00:12:24,650 --> 00:12:29,180
Right. We're keeping a good eye on him.

147
00:12:29,180 --> 00:12:30,920
You did well.

148
00:12:46,790 --> 00:12:49,760
Did Woohyun cry or not?

149
00:12:50,690 --> 00:12:53,830
 (He didn't cry. He didn't cry.)

150
00:13:17,160 --> 00:13:20,060
- Hey, you do it. 
 - Huh?

151
00:13:20,060 --> 00:13:22,420
Okay.

152
00:13:22,420 --> 00:13:26,300
I'm going to tell everybody. That Seulbi's not a thief.

153
00:13:26,300 --> 00:13:29,240
Chunsik, were you bored? You must have been really bored.

154
00:13:29,240 --> 00:13:31,590
I was bored.

155
00:13:38,850 --> 00:13:40,750
Look forward to it.

156
00:13:54,340 --> 00:13:57,530
My hand hurts from writing all this.

157
00:14:05,410 --> 00:14:09,720
Did Chunsik confess? Will we be okay?

158
00:14:09,720 --> 00:14:12,500
As long as you shut your mouth, we'll be okay.

159
00:14:15,340 --> 00:14:20,040
I warned you as to what would happen to a betrayer.

160
00:14:20,040 --> 00:14:22,570
Be careful.

161
00:14:41,590 --> 00:14:51,910

162
00:14:55,100 --> 00:14:57,750
Why do you keep cleaning the area you have already cleaned?

163
00:14:57,750 --> 00:15:01,490
I heard you would have fewer sad thoughts if your body is worn out.

164
00:15:02,720 --> 00:15:05,360
Did you send Grandma off well?

165
00:15:05,360 --> 00:15:06,660
Yeah.

166
00:15:06,660 --> 00:15:08,960
How's Woohyun?

167
00:15:08,960 --> 00:15:13,100
He keeps sleeping. Or he's acting like he is.

168
00:15:13,100 --> 00:15:16,710
Sleep is another way of overcoming sadness.

169
00:15:16,710 --> 00:15:19,140
I see.

170
00:15:19,140 --> 00:15:22,340
You said you were leaving. When are you going back?

171
00:15:22,340 --> 00:15:26,860
Actually, I'm not going to go.

172
00:15:26,860 --> 00:15:28,890
I decided not to go.

173
00:15:31,710 --> 00:15:35,670
That's good. Did you tell the adults?

174
00:15:35,670 --> 00:15:38,750
I don't have any adults to contact.

175
00:15:39,630 --> 00:15:41,810
  You're the same as me.

176
00:15:41,810 --> 00:15:45,540
Why are you here now? Did you not go to school?

177
00:15:45,540 --> 00:15:47,730
I didn't want to go.

178
00:15:47,730 --> 00:15:50,620
You have stuff that you don't want to do, too?

179
00:15:50,620 --> 00:15:52,900
In your eyes, do I seem like a monster?

180
00:15:52,900 --> 00:15:56,450
I'm saying that because you're that perfect.

181
00:15:56,450 --> 00:15:58,800
But is there something wrong?

182
00:15:59,500 --> 00:16:03,510
I just didn't want to go to school today.

183
00:16:03,510 --> 00:16:05,420
Really?

184
00:16:06,350 --> 00:16:10,140
That's a relief. That there isn't anything wrong.

185
00:16:10,840 --> 00:16:13,080
You have to go to school tomorrow.

186
00:16:13,080 --> 00:16:16,360
If you don't go because Woohyun isn't going, you'll get in trouble.

187
00:16:32,500 --> 00:16:37,700
Ms. Gong, you're inside there, right?

188
00:16:40,800 --> 00:16:43,570
You're just sleeping because you're tired, right?

189
00:16:48,420 --> 00:16:50,490
Just once...

190
00:16:51,640 --> 00:16:53,990
Just once...

191
00:16:53,990 --> 00:16:56,710
I wish you could appear again.

192
00:16:59,430 --> 00:17:04,900
Grandma, I couldn't even tell you that I love you.

193
00:17:38,290 --> 00:17:41,640
You weren't at school today. Where did you go?

194
00:17:43,120 --> 00:17:44,310
Do I have to answer?

195
00:17:44,310 --> 00:17:47,490
You should have at least called. I was worried.

196
00:17:49,000 --> 00:17:51,940
If you don't want to go to school, you can rest for a few days.

197
00:17:51,940 --> 00:17:54,080
I'll talk to your father.

198
00:17:54,080 --> 00:17:57,010
Oh, yeah! Did you eat?

199
00:17:57,010 --> 00:17:59,830
Stop trying to act like my mom.

200
00:17:59,830 --> 00:18:03,750
Since Teacher is acting like that, my mother is running away.

201
00:18:04,670 --> 00:18:09,100
I'll just stay next to you as a guardian.

202
00:18:09,870 --> 00:18:12,190
Tired words. Hateful words.

203
00:18:12,190 --> 00:18:15,940
You can spill them out anytime, so don't hold it in.

204
00:18:15,940 --> 00:18:18,610
Please don't do anything.

205
00:18:18,610 --> 00:18:20,690
Absolutely nothing.

206
00:18:24,640 --> 00:18:27,100
Hey, Sungyeol, did you eat...

207
00:18:36,040 --> 00:18:40,180
Get up. Eat at least one spoonful.

208
00:18:41,530 --> 00:18:44,060
Get up.

209
00:18:59,600 --> 00:19:02,530
Now I know what sadness is, too.

210
00:19:04,130 --> 00:19:08,200
I think it's sad that I can't do anything for you.

211
00:19:10,270 --> 00:19:15,310
I miss Grandma, too.

212
00:19:18,420 --> 00:19:22,540
I'll let Grandma know what you want to tell her.

213
00:19:22,540 --> 00:19:25,450
So just get up, Woohyun.

214
00:19:44,900 --> 00:19:54,190

215
00:19:59,750 --> 00:20:02,700
I guess I can't see him anymore.

216
00:20:04,040 --> 00:20:08,370
Senior! Senior.

217
00:20:08,370 --> 00:20:10,610
Can I still see you?

218
00:20:10,610 --> 00:20:13,550
I'm not going to see you, move.

219
00:20:13,550 --> 00:20:15,580
I have something to ask of you.

220
00:20:16,380 --> 00:20:19,940
A human can't ask an angel for a favor.

221
00:20:26,740 --> 00:20:30,880
Grandma, let me see her one more time.

222
00:20:30,880 --> 00:20:34,140
You're asking me to break the rules. I can't.

223
00:20:34,140 --> 00:20:36,960
Even if it's through a dream?

224
00:20:36,960 --> 00:20:40,650
If you just let Woohyun meet her once,

225
00:20:42,330 --> 00:20:45,830
he couldn't even say goodbye properly.

226
00:20:45,830 --> 00:20:50,070
His grandma was the whole world to him,

227
00:20:50,070 --> 00:20:52,900
but that world has disappeared.

228
00:20:53,640 --> 00:20:56,730
So just once,

229
00:20:56,730 --> 00:20:59,020
let him say goodbye to Grandma.

230
00:20:59,020 --> 00:21:03,320
Why are you doing all this for that guy?

231
00:21:03,320 --> 00:21:05,270
I don't know.

232
00:21:06,210 --> 00:21:08,510
I want to do something for him.

233
00:21:08,510 --> 00:21:10,830
I want to do it,

234
00:21:12,320 --> 00:21:14,240
but I can't do anything.

235
00:21:14,240 --> 00:21:16,800
No, it's beyond my own powers.

236
00:21:16,800 --> 00:21:19,180
Then tell her that he loves her...

237
00:21:21,090 --> 00:21:24,200
that Woohyun loves her a lot.

238
00:21:25,300 --> 00:21:28,830
Tell her that he's going to be okay.

239
00:21:28,830 --> 00:21:30,810
I beg of you.

240
00:21:30,810 --> 00:21:34,230
If the human love that you chose changes,

241
00:21:34,230 --> 00:21:37,180
then you will lose the thing that's most precious to you.

242
00:21:37,180 --> 00:21:41,020
That's your punishment for leaving our world,

243
00:21:41,020 --> 00:21:43,260
and the rule of this world.

244
00:21:43,260 --> 00:21:44,900
Something precious?

245
00:21:44,900 --> 00:21:48,110
After you gave up being an angel by breaking your vows,

246
00:21:48,110 --> 00:21:50,500
you should've expected this!

247
00:21:52,960 --> 00:21:55,340
Even if I lose everything,

248
00:21:56,520 --> 00:22:00,340
if Woohyun is happy, then I think I'll be okay.

249
00:22:00,340 --> 00:22:02,290
You're really...

250
00:22:04,140 --> 00:22:06,400
Who are you talking to?

251
00:22:08,370 --> 00:22:10,890
Oh, no one.

252
00:22:15,230 --> 00:22:17,580
Why are you here?

253
00:22:17,580 --> 00:22:19,410
Here?

254
00:22:20,050 --> 00:22:23,100
Because I missed Grandma.

255
00:22:38,890 --> 00:22:40,860
Lee Seulbi.

256
00:22:43,650 --> 00:22:45,640
Lee Seulbi.

257
00:22:52,490 --> 00:22:54,640
Lee Seulbi!

258
00:22:57,550 --> 00:22:59,930
 Even if I lose everything,

259
00:23:01,060 --> 00:23:05,640
 if Woohyun is happy, then I think I'll be okay.

260
00:23:07,190 --> 00:23:08,940
Lose?

261
00:23:10,090 --> 00:23:12,670
Even if she loses everything, she'll still like Woohyun?

262
00:23:12,670 --> 00:23:15,560
I'll lose something precious?

263
00:23:20,040 --> 00:23:22,930
- Woohyun! 
 - You...

