♫  ...along the river that sparkles in the sun   ♫

590
00:45:49,660 --> 00:45:52,940
Bongie!

591
00:45:52,940 --> 00:45:54,030
Bongie!

592
00:45:54,030 --> 00:46:04,990
♫  Your scent that envelopes me    ♫

593
00:46:04,990 --> 00:46:07,290
♫  You and I, just us two   ♫

594
00:46:07,290 --> 00:46:09,360
Bongie!

595
00:46:09,360 --> 00:46:12,580
Bongie!

596
00:46:12,580 --> 00:46:15,920
Bongie!

597
00:46:15,920 --> 00:46:20,770
♫   ...blue sky with white clouds  ♫

598
00:46:20,770 --> 00:46:22,080
Bongie!

599
00:46:22,080 --> 00:46:31,730
♫  ...and with the warm wind brushing against our clothes   ♫

600
00:46:31,730 --> 00:46:38,960
♫  I look at her with a bright face  ♫

601
00:47:07,980 --> 00:47:10,070
Seulbi!

602
00:47:10,070 --> 00:47:12,550
Lee Seulbi!

603
00:47:15,660 --> 00:47:17,930
Give this to Seulbi.

604
00:47:17,930 --> 00:47:19,750
You give it to her personally.

605
00:47:19,750 --> 00:47:22,520
Were you always this insensitive?

606
00:47:22,520 --> 00:47:26,860
Seulbi has been working from dawn to night to repay the debt.

607
00:47:26,860 --> 00:47:30,260
Her body smells like pain relief patches!

608
00:47:30,260 --> 00:47:32,230
Stop acting so childish!

609
00:47:32,230 --> 00:47:34,960
Childish?

610
00:47:34,960 --> 00:47:39,540
Just because you have so much, do I seem childish to you because I'm acting like this over one loss?

611
00:47:39,540 --> 00:47:41,570
Because of you, Seulbi couldn't leave!

612
00:47:41,570 --> 00:47:42,870
I never told her to stay.

613
00:47:42,870 --> 00:47:46,150
You never told her to leave sincerely, either.

614
00:47:46,150 --> 00:47:50,510
Stop acting like you're the most pitiful guy in this world!

615
00:47:50,510 --> 00:47:52,630
You received a lot of love from your grandma. I—

616
00:47:52,630 --> 00:47:54,390
If you're done, go away.

617
00:47:54,390 --> 00:47:56,610
I still have more.

618
00:47:56,610 --> 00:47:58,960
I can't stand this anymore,

619
00:47:58,960 --> 00:48:01,870
so stay away from Seulbi.

620
00:48:04,760 --> 00:48:10,890
Because of guys like you, hardworking Seulbi is pitiful.

621
00:48:21,500 --> 00:48:27,820
If I find lost dogs for people every day, I'll be able to pay off the debt pretty soon.

622
00:48:27,820 --> 00:48:31,380
It hurts.

623
00:48:41,000 --> 00:48:44,470
Ms. Gong,

624
00:48:44,470 --> 00:48:47,480
I should have told you that you were pretty.

625
00:49:12,000 --> 00:49:17,500
You didn't even know that you were sick because you were earning and saving up this money?

626
00:49:17,500 --> 00:49:22,400
We should have gone on a world trip with this money.

627
00:49:22,510 --> 00:49:26,500
We didn't even get to go to Jeju Island.

628
00:49:26,500 --> 00:49:30,100
We're really stupid.

629
00:49:33,200 --> 00:49:35,920
We have so much money saved,

630
00:49:35,920 --> 00:49:39,450
yet why don't we have any memories?

631
00:49:52,250 --> 00:49:53,960
Really...

632
00:49:53,960 --> 00:49:56,550
Move.

633
00:49:56,550 --> 00:50:00,380
I'll earn and pay you back the remaining sum.

634
00:50:05,920 --> 00:50:08,380
Are you playing with me?

635
00:50:08,380 --> 00:50:10,210
You will never be able to pay up.

636
00:50:10,210 --> 00:50:12,700
I'll try my best.

637
00:50:12,700 --> 00:50:15,750
By using whatever means, I'll make sure to repay you.

638
00:50:15,750 --> 00:50:19,900
What "means" will you use to pay us back?

639
00:50:19,930 --> 00:50:22,950
Pay for this as well.

640
00:50:22,950 --> 00:50:25,120
I'm sorry.

641
00:50:25,120 --> 00:50:26,240
I'm sorry.

642
00:50:26,240 --> 00:50:28,320
Wait a minute.

643
00:50:30,690 --> 00:50:34,890
You are pretty.

644
00:50:38,030 --> 00:50:44,350
Little girl, there are actually a lot of ways to make money.

645
00:50:46,540 --> 00:50:47,710
Woohyun!

646
00:50:47,710 --> 00:50:50,400
You're scary.

647
00:50:50,400 --> 00:50:53,160
You think you're all that?

648
00:50:57,140 --> 00:51:03,620
Look at this. Money can make a person kneel.

649
00:51:03,620 --> 00:51:06,220
Let's repay the borrowed money, okay?

650
00:51:06,220 --> 00:51:08,540
If you don't pay up...

651
00:51:08,540 --> 00:51:12,350
You know, right?

652
00:51:19,620 --> 00:51:23,830
If we try our best, we'll be able to get them back soon:

653
00:51:23,830 --> 00:51:29,660
the house and the store.

654
00:51:29,660 --> 00:51:33,960
There are a lot of places high schoolers can go to earn money.

655
00:51:33,960 --> 00:51:37,670
- You and I... 
 - Should we spend our whole life paying back the debt?

656
00:51:37,670 --> 00:51:39,100
Is that your dream?

657
00:51:39,100 --> 00:51:40,860
Your wish?

658
00:51:40,860 --> 00:51:43,560
Then you do it.

659
00:51:43,560 --> 00:51:44,490
Woohyun.

660
00:51:44,490 --> 00:51:46,160
I don't need anything anymore.

661
00:51:46,160 --> 00:51:49,070
I don't need it at all!

662
00:51:56,420 --> 00:52:02,740
Have you ever thought how heartbroken Grandma would be if she ever saw you like this?

663
00:52:02,740 --> 00:52:09,040
I'm hurting, too, because I've been left behind. I'm hurting so much I could die!

664
00:52:09,040 --> 00:52:11,960
Do you not see me?

665
00:52:11,960 --> 00:52:14,510
You're not alone.

666
00:52:14,510 --> 00:52:16,550
What about me?

667
00:52:16,550 --> 00:52:20,180
I didn't want you to be alone,

668
00:52:20,180 --> 00:52:24,780
so I gave up everything.

669
00:52:24,780 --> 00:52:27,520
Don't be like this, Woohyun.

670
00:52:27,520 --> 00:52:29,400
So leave.

671
00:52:29,400 --> 00:52:33,560
Please just leave!

672
00:52:57,740 --> 00:53:00,970
